quran[18]{c,v,t,f}:
  68,43,"Their eyes will be downcast, overwhelmed with humiliation, for they were invited to prostrate when they were capable<sup>10</sup> [but they refused].","[10] During the life of this world."
  68,44,"So leave to Me those who reject this message [O Prophet]. We will gradually lead them to their ruin in ways that they do not perceive<sup>11</sup>.","[11] Allah will increase favors upon them in this life as a trial, so they will increase sin, which will lead to their destruction."
  68,45,"I will give them respite, but My plan is firm.",""
  68,46,"Or are you asking them for a reward, so they find it too burdensome?",""
  68,47,"Or do they have knowledge of the unseen, so they write it down?",""
  68,48,"So be patient with the decree of your Lord, and do not be like the man of the Whale [i.e., Jonah], when he cried out in anguish<sup>12</sup>.","[12] While inside the belly of the whale. See 21:87 and 37:139-148."
  68,49,"Had it not been for the grace that he received from his Lord, he would have surely been thrown onto the barren shore, blameworthy<sup>13</sup>.","[13] Instead, Allah accepted his repentance and provided for him means of recovery. See 37:139-148."
  68,50,"But his Lord chose him and made him one of the righteous.",""
  68,51,"The disbelievers would almost strike you down with their malicious gazes when they hear the Reminder, and they say, “He is certainly mad.”",""
  68,52,"But it is nothing other than a reminder to the whole world.",""
  69,1,"The Inevitable Hour!",""
  69,2,"What is the Inevitable Hour?",""
  69,3,"How do you know what the Inevitable Hour is?",""
  69,4,"Thamūd and ‘Ād denied the Striking Calamity of the Hour<sup>1</sup>.","[1] The Striking Calamity is one of the names of the Day of Judgment."
  69,5,"As for Thamūd, they were destroyed by a dreadful blast.",""
  69,6,"And as for ‘Ād, they were destroyed by a furious windstorm<sup>2</sup>","[2] Or by a cold windstorm."
  69,7,"which He unleashed against them for seven successive nights and eight days, so you would see the people lying dead as if they were hollow trunks of palm trees.",""
  69,8,"Do you see any trace of them now?",""
